{
  "stem": "14613.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the Lodz ghetto till the fall of 1944, when they liquidated the Lodz ghetto completely.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This-- this, in a way, makes a tremendous distinction between a concentration camp [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because in the ghetto, we were with the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How bad, how miserable the conditions were in the ghetto, you came home to your family-- which you did not have in the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The second thing, at least in the ghetto where I was, that we did not participate, and we were not part of the daily brutality which existed in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I would say, if I look backwards, these were the two main distinctions between the Lodz ghetto for our family, and the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because you have to realize that many families in Lodz ghetto were sent out on the aussiedlung and so on, that their experiences would be different from ours.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were-- there were all the time some kind of aussiedlungs, that-- that we, as such, living there in ghetto, did not know all the time, but we knew that they are in existence all the time.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they would-- they would ask different people to-- to appear in certain places that did not work or to say, and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they appeared all the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, personally, I did not know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Looking back, I know from history there have been some people that had clandestine radios and so on, but-- but we, our family, we did not know about it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a well-hidden secret.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't think about future in the ghetto-- maybe in the very beginning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You don't think about the future, and even less so later on in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
